closed_at: "2026-07-17T23:53:19.762Z"
author: maintainer-agent
estimated_minutes: 90
acceptance_criteria: tools/call surfaces a warning (matching the pm-qxwu top-level mechanism) for every options key absent from the invoked action's contract; contract tables stay the single source of truth; regression test covers a mutation-shaped key on a read tool
parent: pm-96h7
risk: low
confidence: high
resolution: "Contract-driven nested-option validation in mcp/server.ts: detectUnexpectedOptionKeys warns (warn-only, pm-qxwu style) for every options key absent from the invoked action's contract, single-sourced from pmToolActionParameterKeys"
expected_result: pm_deps options.dep (and any unknown nested option key on a contract-described action) surfaces an explicit warning instead of silently no-opping
actual_result: Warning emitted on stderr and in structuredContent.warnings with did-you-mean suggestion and declared-key list; call still succeeds; extension/package actions unaffected; verified live in an MCP session and by regression spec
